Sentencas: High performance anode materials with suitable thermal and chemical expansions are highly desirable for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this work, we report a promising anode material La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (LSFM) synthesized in nitrogen at 1050 degrees C. Its phase stability, mechanical behavior, redox stability, and electrochemical performance were studied.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of LSFM reaches 23 S cm(-1) in 5% H-2-95% N-2 at 800 degrees C with excellent reversibility over three redox cycles.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: After lanthanum doping, the coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) is reduced from 17.12 x 10(-6) K-1 (SF1.5M) to 15.01 x 10(-6) K-1 (LSFM), and this value can be lowered further with a higher lanthanum content.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Dilatometry testing at 800 degrees C shows that the chemical expansion behavior of LSFM is highly reversible during the oxidation-reduction cycling.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that the thermal and chemical expansion of the crystal lattice can be reduced by a stronger metal-oxygen (M-O) bond strength, leading to an improvement in redox reversibility.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the LSFM symmetrical cell at 800 degrees C in humidified hydrogen is 0.16 Omega cm(2), and the active region is similar to 4.5 mu m.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The half-tear-drop-shaped impedance spectroscopy indicates an oxygen bulk diffusion and surface reaction colimited process.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the LSFM single cell reaches 1156 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C within humidified H-2.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The new ceramic material LSFM is a promising anode for high performance solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Reduced Thermal Expansion and Enhanced Redox Reversibility of La0.5Sr1.5Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
